title: Clinical Safety Alerts Index
titlePt: Indice de Alertas Clinicos de Seguranca
description: Master index of all clinical safety alerts for patient care. These rules are designed to prevent adverse drug events, detect critical conditions, monitor vital signs, identify clinical syndromes, and ensure patient safety through evidence-based decision support.
descriptionPt: Indice mestre de todos os alertas clinicos de seguranca para assistencia ao paciente. Estas regras sao projetadas para prevenir eventos adversos a medicamentos, detectar condicoes criticas, monitorar sinais vitais, identificar sindromes clinicas e garantir seguranca do paciente atraves de suporte a decisao baseado em evidencias.

DDI.name: Drug-Drug Interactions
DDI.description: Detection of dangerous drug-drug interactions including serotonin syndrome, QT prolongation, bleeding risk, hepatotoxicity, and nephrotoxicity

DDX.name: Disease-Drug Contraindications
DDX.description: Detection of contraindicated medications based on patient disease states and comorbidities

DLI.name: Drug-Lab Interactions
DLI.description: Dose adjustments and monitoring requirements based on renal function (eGFR/CrCl), hepatic function (Child-Pugh), and electrolyte abnormalities

EWS.name: Early Warning Scores
EWS.description: Validated early warning scoring systems: NEWS2 for adults, PEWS for pediatrics, MEWS modified, qSOFA for sepsis screening

LAB.name: Critical Laboratory Values
LAB.description: Detection of critical and panic laboratory values requiring immediate clinical intervention

MED.name: Medication Safety
MED.description: Medication dosing validation, duplicate therapy detection, high-alert medication protocols

RSK.name: Risk Assessment Scores
RSK.description: Clinical risk assessment tools: HAS-BLED, Morse Fall Scale, Braden Pressure Ulcer, Caprini VTE

SYN.name: Clinical Syndromes
SYN.description: Detection of critical clinical syndromes: Sepsis (qSOFA/SOFA), Acute Kidney Injury (KDIGO), Myocardial Infarction, DKA, VTE

VIT.name: Vital Signs Monitoring
VIT.description: Critical vital sign alerts, pediatric-specific thresholds, and trend analysis for early deterioration detection

regulations: RDC 36/2013 - Seguranca do Paciente em Servicos de Saude

impactAnalysis.patientSafetyImpact: Critical - Direct prevention of adverse drug events, early detection of clinical deterioration, and timely intervention for life-threatening conditions
impactAnalysis.adverseEventPrevention: Estimated 30-50% reduction in preventable adverse drug events through real-time clinical decision support
impactAnalysis.mortalityReduction: Estimated 15-25% reduction in sepsis mortality through early detection (qSOFA/NEWS2)
impactAnalysis.medicationErrorPrevention: Estimated 40-60% reduction in significant drug-drug interactions through proactive alerting
impactAnalysis.clinicalWorkflow: Integrated into ordering workflow, nursing assessment, and pharmacy verification

nivelAlerta.description: Alert severity level for clinical action

justificativaCientifica.description: Scientific rationale with literature references and sensitivity/specificity data
